article.headline: SE Louisiana 42, Louisiana Monroe 40
article.story: HAMMOND, La. (AP) -- Ricky Woods failed to score in double digits for the first time in 35 games, but grabbed a pair of rebounds in the final seconds to help Southeastern Louisiana to a 42-40 win over Louisiana-Monroe. Woods grabbed 13 rebounds, including a pair off the offensive glass in the final 3.8 seconds, while Quenell Green scored 13 points to lead the Lions (13-11, 7-6 Southland), who had their poorest shooting effort of the season, finishing 17-for-58 (29 percent) from the floor. Tied 40-40 in the final minute, Jonathan Walker was fouled with 5.3 seconds left. Walker made his first free throw to put Southeastern Louisiana up 41-40, but missed the second attempt. Woods grabbed the rebound while being forced out of bounds and then called timeout, giving the Lions the ball. Micheal Cyprien was fouled on the ensuing play and made the first of his two free throws. Woods was there again for his last rebound and dribbled out to midcourt to preserve the win. Gary Robinson led the Indians with 11 points.
